to layer realized in the iron pnictide The spectrum in superconductors is strongly renormalized due to the electromagnetic interactions between the oscillating magnetic This leads to a strong enhancement of the frequency of the mode coupled with a uniform field and this enhancement exists only within a narrow range of the wave vectors of the order of the inverse London penetration The key superconductors and study the interplay between the features and geometrical cavity resonances in the less Condensed Matter Physics December , 9:03pm Interplay between superconductivity and magnetic place inside superconducting state and the exchange interaction between superconducting and magnetic subsystems is weak so that superconductivity ... more We consider a clean layered magnetic superconductor in which a continuous magnetic transition takes place inside superconducting state and the exchange interaction between superconducting and magnetic subsystems is weak so that superconductivity is not destroyed at the magnetic An example of such material is We investigate the suppression of the superconducting gap and superfluid density by correlated magnetic fluctuations in the vicinity of the magnetic The influence of nonuniform exchange field on superconducting parameters is sensitive to the relation between the magnetic correlation length, Œæh, and superconducting coherence length Œæs defining the scattering (Œæh<Œæs) and smooth (Œæh Œæs) As a small uniform exchange field does not affect the superconducting gap and superfluid density at zero temperature, smoothening of the spatial variations of the exchange field reduces its effects on these We develop a quantitative description of this scattering-to-smooth crossover for the case of magnetic Since the probability varies at the energy scale comparable with the gap, the quasiclassical approximation is not applicable in the crossover region and microscopic treatment is We find that the corrections to both the gap and superfluid density grow proportionally to Œæh until it remains much smaller than When Œæh exceeds Œæs, both parameters have much weaker dependence on Moreover, the gap correction may decrease with increasing of Œæh in the vicinity of the magnetic We also find that the crossover is unexpectedly broad: the standard scattering approximation becomes sufficient only when Œæh is Anyone in our growing service area qualifies, with pilot programs launching in Wrangell and Sitka in early Is Tidal Network available in other locations in Southeast Alaska? Tidal Network aims to expand coverage to unserved communities in Southeast Alaska when funding is New sites will be added to our coverage map as they come Pilot programs are launching in Wrangell and Sitka in early Why should I choose Tidal Network over other providers? Tidal Network is unique in that our primary goal is to provide broadband access to communities and households that were previously However, customers with access to other internet service providers may still choose Tidal Network for other reasons, such as available support services or discounted service When will services start? Tidal Network is targeting early for launch of services in Wrangell and Sitka, depending on the supply When can I enroll and what is the enrollment and installation process? Tidal Network will visit the communities in person to launch and initiate the enrollment An online tool will be available as How can I get service through Tidal Network if I‚Äôm not in Wrangell? Tidal Network will advertise as new communities are added to our internet service provider (ISP) Other services, such as remote technical support and managed , may be available immediately to anyone with existing phone or internet I‚Äôm a Wrangell How do I connect with customer service in Wrangell? Access to the customer application for parental security, usage data, and connectivity status will be provided to each customer and managed by Tidal How can I access additional services? Reunion - marketplace for renewable energy tax credits WHAT WE DO ABOUT FAQ CONTACT Accelerating RENEWABLE energY BY simplifying FINANCING WHAT WE DO Reunion√¢¬Ä¬ôs mission is to accelerate renewable energy by simplifying The Inflation Reduction Act allows transferability of renewable energy tax credits, which will dramatically accelerate renewable We are building a marketplace where corporations can purchase vetted tax credits from solar, wind, and battery storage Reunion√¢¬Ä¬ôs platform makes transactions easy and low Corporations can reduce their federal tax liability, while enabling new renewable energy Solar, wind, and battery storage companies can sell transferable tax credits, without the complexity and hassle of traditional tax equity financing ABOUT US Reunion√¢¬Ä¬ôs founders, Andy Moon and Billy Lee , have deep experience in tax equity and structured We pioneered some of the earliest solar energy financings, and have collectively raised over $2B to construct solar energy projects around the Andy and Billy are both entrepreneurs, and have served in executive roles at We are backed by√Ç Segue Sustainable Infrastructure, and leading renewable energy entrepreneurs and √¢¬Ä¬ç Xxxxxxxxx FAQ What are renewable energy tax credits? Renewable energy projects such as solar and wind typically rely on tax credits to fund up to % of the project Starting in , the Inflation Reduction Act (IRA) will offer % to % tax credits for renewable energy projects, which will accelerate the speed of renewable energy Tax credits play a significant role in making renewable energy projects economical without them, many renewable energy projects will not get Why is Reunion focused on renewable energy tax credits? Historically, the only way to monetize tax credits are through complicated tax equity partnerships, which have only been available to the largest projects developed by established The IRA now allows the sale of tax credits at a market price, bypassing need for complex This will unlock many new renewable energy projects that previously lacked access to Why hasn t this been done before? The Inflation Reduction Act, passed in August , for the first time allows renewable energy tax credits to be bought and sold, for projects that are placed in service starting January 1, Reunion is the first marketplace to buy and sell transferable tax credits generated by renewable infrastructure Why buy a renewable energy tax credit? Tax credits are used to reduce federal tax Because tax credits will typically sell for a discount, the buyer can make a profit (e.g., buyer pays ~$9M in cash for $10M worth of tax credits). Purchasing a tax credit supports the construction of new renewable energy projects, which may not be economical without revenues from sale of the tax Who can buy a renewable energy tax credit? Most US corporations can use renewable energy tax credits to reduce their federal taxes dollar for dollar (e.g., $100 of tax credits reduces tax liabilities by $100). Individuals can use tax credits to offset tax liability arising from passive income (e.g., real estate holdings). Certain individuals that work in the solar wind industry may be able to offset tax liability arising from active What types of projects are eligible? Reunion is focused on solar, wind, battery storage, and EV We are not working on hydrogen, carbon capture, or other technologies at this time share your email below to stay in touch Thank you!
